cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with depth sensing cameras and upsampling of depth maps using high resolution color images. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with improving the quality of depth maps, which is a crucial component in computer graphics applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image guided depth upsampling, which is a multimedia processing task. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - Depth sensing cameras are widely used in robotics applications for obstacle detection and navigation. Improving the quality of depth maps can have significant impact on the performance of such systems. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel optimization framework for depth upsampling, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
